sec.p:
By definition, the energy efficiency (EE) is calculated as the system throughput over the
     total power consumption [50, Eq. (3)].  \begin{align*} \mathsf {EE}=\frac{\mathrm{\tau
       _{BS}}}{\text {P}_{s}}, \tag{15} \end{align*}

app.p:
By means of [39, Eq. (1.110)],
       $\mathcal {I}_{7}$ is
     further simplified as  \begin{align*}
       &\sum _{u=0}^{\infty }\frac{\Gamma (\frac{a+2k+5}{2})}{\Gamma (u+1)\Gamma
       (\frac{a+2k-2u+5}{2})}\underbrace{\int _{0}^{\infty }\gamma _{F}^{M+u-1}e^{-\frac{\gamma
       _{F}}{\text {P}_{J}\Omega _{m}}}d\gamma _{F}}_{\mathcal {I}_{8}}. \tag{35} \end{align*}

By definition [60, Eq. (11)], (38) is obtained as:  \begin{align*} F_{\text {A}}^{\text {a}}\left(\gamma
       \right)=\rho -\rho \frac{\Gamma (a+1,\frac{\gamma }{\rho b})}{\Gamma (a+1)}. \tag{39}
       \end{align*}

By means of [59, Eq. (06.06.06.0001.02)],
       $F_{A}^{\text {a}}(\gamma)=\rho (\frac{\gamma
       }{\rho b})^{a+1}/\Gamma (a+1)(a+1)$. Utilizing the obtained
     results in (39), following expressions are
     obtained.  \begin{align*} F\gamma _{\text
       {BS}}^{\text {a}}\left(\gamma \right)=F_{\text {A}}^{\text {a}}\left(\left(\frac{\gamma
       }{\text {P}_{s}}\left(\rho ^{2}\gamma _{G}+\gamma _{F}+1\right)\right)^{\frac{1}{2}}\right).
       \tag{40} \end{align*}

Substituting the related PDF expressions into (47), $\mathcal
      {I}_{13}$ is written as  \begin{align*} &\left(\frac{1}{\text {P}_{J}\Omega
       _{m}}\right)^{M}\frac{1}{\Gamma (M)}\\ &\times \underbrace{\int _{0}^{\infty
       }\left(\gamma _{F}+1\right)^{\frac{a+1}{2}}\gamma _{F}^{M-1}e^{-\frac{\gamma _{F}}{\text
       {P}_{J}\Omega _{m}}}d\gamma _{F}}_{\mathcal {I}_{14}}. \tag{48} \end{align*}

By means of [39, Eq. (1.110)],
       $\mathcal {I}_{14}$ is
     further simplified as  \begin{align*}
       &\sum _{u=0}^{\infty }\frac{\Gamma (\frac{a+3}{2})}{\Gamma (u+1)\Gamma
       (\frac{a+3-2u}{2})}\underbrace{\int _{0}^{\infty }\gamma _{F}^{M+u-1}e^{-\frac{\gamma
       _{F}}{\text {P}_{J}\Omega _{m}}}d\gamma _{F}}_{\mathcal {I}_{15}}, \tag{49} \end{align*}
      Since $(a+1)/2$ is not an integer in $\binom{\frac{a+1}{2}}{u}$,
       $\binom{x}{y}=\frac{\Gamma (x+1)}{\Gamma
       (y+1)\Gamma (x-y+1)}$[39] is utilized for the further simplification. By means of [39, Eq. (3.381.4)], the integral expressions in $\mathcal {I}_{15}$ are solved as  \begin{align*} \mathcal {I}_{15}=\frac{\Gamma
       (M+u)}{\left(\frac{1}{\text {P}_{J}\Omega _{m}}\right)^{M+u}}. \tag{50} \end{align*}

Starting with the active RIS when the source has a LOS link with the destination terminal,
     substituting the related CDF expression, (5),
     into EP formula, (9), following integral
     expression is obtained  \begin{align*}
       \bar{\text {P}_{e}}^{a+d}=\frac{1}{2\sqrt{\pi }}\int _{0}^{\infty }\gamma
       ^{\frac{a+2k+2}{2}}\text {exp}(-\gamma)d\gamma. \tag{51} \end{align*}
